00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:36,266 --> 00:00:39,060
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

2
00:00:40,812 --> 00:00:44,274
<i>Before enlisting, I had five million won,</i>

3
00:00:44,357 --> 00:00:46,276
<i>so I put it into stocks.</i>

4
00:00:46,901 --> 00:00:48,069
<i>When I got discharged…</i>

5
00:00:48,152 --> 00:00:49,320
<i>Ta-da.</i>

6
00:00:49,988 --> 00:00:51,698
<i>It increased to 30 million.</i>

7
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:53,616
<i>Yes, 30 million.</i>

8
00:00:54,617 --> 00:00:55,827
<i>Right then,</i>

9
00:00:55,910 --> 00:00:57,829
<i>do you know what my biggest worry was?</i>

10
00:00:59,330 --> 00:01:01,332
<i>"I'm the only one</i>
<i>who knows about this money."</i>

11
00:01:02,292 --> 00:01:03,501
<i>"What if I die?"</i>

12
00:01:05,753 --> 00:01:06,754
<i>Then one day…</i>

13
00:01:08,923 --> 00:01:10,175
<i>a burglar tried to break in.</i>

14
00:01:12,886 --> 00:01:14,554
<i>I saw something like a knife,</i>

15
00:01:15,388 --> 00:01:17,098
<i>and my heart started pounding.</i>

16
00:01:18,016 --> 00:01:19,017
<i>I didn't know what to do.</i>

17
00:01:20,185 --> 00:01:21,352
<i>At that moment,</i>

18
00:01:21,436 --> 00:01:23,855
<i>I thought of the 30 million won I had.</i>

19
00:01:31,112 --> 00:01:31,988
<i>I thought, "I can't die."</i>

20
00:01:32,906 --> 00:01:34,407
<i>"I have 30 million won."</i>

21
00:01:36,034 --> 00:01:39,370
<i>Even though I hadn't eaten or slept,</i>

22
00:01:39,454 --> 00:01:40,705
<i>I was full of energy.</i>

23
00:01:41,998 --> 00:01:43,374
<i>That 30 million won</i>

24
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:45,543
<i>made me feel like I had superpowers.</i>

25
00:01:48,004 --> 00:01:49,047
<i>But then…</i>

26
00:01:51,758 --> 00:01:53,259
<i>it increased to 50 million won.</i>

27
00:02:08,191 --> 00:02:09,150
<i>Suddenly,</i>

28
00:02:09,692 --> 00:02:11,569
<i>everything became easy.</i>

29
00:02:13,863 --> 00:02:17,533
<i>It felt like</i>
<i>nothing in life stood in my way.</i>

30
00:02:20,328 --> 00:02:21,204
Dong-man.

31
00:02:23,414 --> 00:02:25,041
Let's step into the center…

32
00:02:27,919 --> 00:02:28,836
of history.

33
00:02:37,553 --> 00:02:38,429
<i>Hey, Hwang.</i>

34
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:40,139
<i>Want to try taking a photo?</i>

35
00:02:44,936 --> 00:02:47,105
<i>You were such a beautiful young man.</i>

36
00:02:48,314 --> 00:02:49,482
<i>I'll bear that in mind.</i>

37
00:02:49,565 --> 00:02:51,818
<i>I can see the universe in your face.</i>

38
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:54,570
<i>From what angle and in what way</i>

39
00:02:54,654 --> 00:02:57,490
<i>can I capture</i>
<i>the depth of the universe inside you?</i>

40
00:02:58,074 --> 00:03:01,577
<i>I ponder over this every day</i>
<i>while watching all of your films.</i>

41
00:03:01,661 --> 00:03:02,829
<i>He really is a crazy bastard.</i>

42
00:03:02,912 --> 00:03:04,122
<i>After watching you every day,</i>

43
00:03:04,205 --> 00:03:07,125
<i>I'm beginning to mix up your face</i>

44
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:08,459
<i>with mine.</i>

45
00:03:09,961 --> 00:03:12,547
HWANG DONG-MAN: HEHEHE

46
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:15,091
Seriously, this little punk.

47
00:03:17,135 --> 00:03:18,011
MR. NOH KANG-SIK

48
00:03:18,094 --> 00:03:19,303
<i>Stop messaging me.</i>

49
00:03:21,472 --> 00:03:23,016
Who does he think he is?

50
00:03:23,099 --> 00:03:25,518
<i>How dare you have the audacity</i>
<i>to babble on like that?</i>

51
00:03:25,601 --> 00:03:26,436
<i>Yes, sir!</i>

52
00:03:26,519 --> 00:03:27,770
<i>I got excited</i>

53
00:03:27,854 --> 00:03:30,606
<i>because I have the top actor Noh Kang-sik</i>
<i>in my contacts.</i>

54
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:31,524
Damn it.

55
00:03:31,607 --> 00:03:32,900
<i>That's it for today.</i>

56
00:03:33,609 --> 00:03:34,652
Jeez.

57
00:03:36,362 --> 00:03:38,156
Director, let's take five.

58
00:04:03,931 --> 00:04:05,641
DEPOSIT AMOUNT: 20,000,000 WON
SENDER: HWANG DONG-MAN

59
00:04:05,725 --> 00:04:06,684
What's this?

60
00:04:07,393 --> 00:04:08,478
You're saving 100 million won

61
00:04:09,896 --> 00:04:11,105
to give Yeong-sil when you see her.

62
00:04:12,774 --> 00:04:13,775
I'm going to chip in.

63
00:04:14,859 --> 00:04:15,902
I got my signing fee.

64
00:04:17,111 --> 00:04:18,363
My film's going into production.

65
00:04:28,122 --> 00:04:29,248
DEPOSIT AMOUNT: 20,000,000 WON
SENDER: HWANG JIN-MAN

66
00:04:29,332 --> 00:04:30,458
Why?

67
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,211
If you have money,
get your own place and move out.

68
00:04:33,795 --> 00:04:34,837
Live your own life,

69
00:04:34,921 --> 00:04:36,506
and don't worry about mine.

70
00:04:37,924 --> 00:04:39,217
Can't you let me feel grand for once?

71
00:04:40,802 --> 00:04:43,846
I felt grand all night
thinking about chipping in.

72
00:04:45,056 --> 00:04:47,141
Don't stomp on my grandeur.

73
00:04:48,226 --> 00:04:49,519
Don't send it.

74
00:04:51,604 --> 00:04:52,814
We might not even find her!

75
00:04:52,897 --> 00:04:54,899
Of course, we'll find her!

76
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:57,985
If we can't find her, she'll find you!

77
00:04:58,569 --> 00:04:59,946
Don't you think she wants to see her dad?

78
00:05:33,479 --> 00:05:34,730
Are you meeting someone?

79
00:05:38,985 --> 00:05:39,819
I'll get going now.

80
00:05:39,902 --> 00:05:40,862
I'll come back tomorrow.

81
00:05:40,945 --> 00:05:42,196
All right, go on.

82
00:05:57,336 --> 00:05:58,921
It's cold. Why didn't you wait inside?

83
00:06:00,464 --> 00:06:01,674
I just got here.

84
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,467
You always say that.

85
00:06:05,970 --> 00:06:07,138
Your nose is red.

86
00:06:09,432 --> 00:06:10,683
I really did just get here.

87
00:06:15,313 --> 00:06:16,689
Now that Noh Kang-sik is on board,

88
00:06:17,315 --> 00:06:19,483
I'm worried it might be too successful.

89
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:22,069
How will I handle everyone's envy

90
00:06:22,153 --> 00:06:23,279
and jealousy?

91
00:06:23,863 --> 00:06:26,824
Park Gyeong-se is probably
seething with envy right now.

92
00:06:26,908 --> 00:06:28,743
What do I even do when I see his face?

93
00:06:29,493 --> 00:06:30,494
Also,

94
00:06:30,578 --> 00:06:34,916
what if I become so successful
that I suddenly lose my "nobody" charm?

95
00:06:36,375 --> 00:06:39,545
I'm scatterbrained and all over the place,
but I'm not unhappy.

96
00:06:40,213 --> 00:06:42,465
This is my identity and charm.

97
00:06:42,548 --> 00:06:43,925
If I become too successful,

98
00:06:44,008 --> 00:06:46,928
I'm afraid I'll suddenly lose my charm.

99
00:06:47,803 --> 00:06:49,222
You know what I mean.

100
00:06:49,305 --> 00:06:52,767
It's like a character
who starts out as a charming troublemaker

101
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:56,646
but becomes serious and dull
toward the end.

102
00:06:56,729 --> 00:06:58,689
I'm afraid I'll end up dull like that.

103
00:06:58,773 --> 00:07:01,484
Isn't it weird
how all successful people are dull?

104
00:07:02,485 --> 00:07:04,362
Of all the pointless worries
I've heard so far,

105
00:07:04,445 --> 00:07:05,905
this is the most pointless one.

106
00:07:06,489 --> 00:07:07,448
Right?

107
00:07:08,407 --> 00:07:12,828
Even if I succeed,
I'll still be a scatterbrained, crazy guy

108
00:07:12,912 --> 00:07:13,955
who's all over the place.

109
00:07:19,085 --> 00:07:20,503
I'm going to be successful too.

110
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:22,421
Will I lose my charm as well?

111
00:07:27,301 --> 00:07:29,095
Wait. Are you saying I'll lose it?

112
00:07:29,679 --> 00:07:31,430
I wouldn't say you'll lose it.

113
00:07:31,514 --> 00:07:33,057
-It's just…
-It's just what?

114
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:35,851
You'll become less approachable.

115
00:07:35,935 --> 00:07:38,062
It's difficult enough
to approach you right now.

116
00:07:38,145 --> 00:07:40,648
Oh, I don't mean
you're uncomfortable to be around.

117
00:07:40,731 --> 00:07:42,275
It's like

118
00:07:42,358 --> 00:07:45,570
you're on a completely
different level from me.

119
00:07:46,946 --> 00:07:49,991
I still remember how shocked I was
the first time I saw you.

120
00:07:50,575 --> 00:07:53,452
It was like seeing an ideal face
sent from heaven.

121
00:07:54,870 --> 00:07:57,248
"Let this be called a face."

122
00:07:57,331 --> 00:07:59,041
"This is a face,

123
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:01,961
so let all faces resemble it."

124
00:08:04,005 --> 00:08:06,424
They can resemble it,
but they can never be the same.

125
00:08:07,466 --> 00:08:09,677
The moment they become the same,
it's no longer ideal.

126
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:12,013
An ideal is something
you can never fully achieve.

127
00:08:12,597 --> 00:08:14,140
That's what it means, right?

128
00:08:15,182 --> 00:08:16,642
That's the kind of face I saw.

129
00:08:17,268 --> 00:08:18,728
It feels like a miracle

130
00:08:18,811 --> 00:08:21,439
sitting here talking to you
when you once felt unapproachable.

131
00:08:22,023 --> 00:08:23,232
On top of that, you write well.

132
00:08:24,275 --> 00:08:25,943
Can you stop being so perfect?

133
00:08:26,861 --> 00:08:28,529
You almost feel unreal.

134
00:08:31,407 --> 00:08:32,825
Are you worshipping me?

135
00:08:34,410 --> 00:08:36,537
You're an ideal sent down by the gods,

136
00:08:36,621 --> 00:08:38,164
so of course, you deserve worship.

137
00:08:45,504 --> 00:08:46,881
You know your share is included

138
00:08:46,964 --> 00:08:48,591
in the money I received, right?

139
00:08:50,468 --> 00:08:52,595
Tell me whatever it is you want.

140
00:08:52,678 --> 00:08:53,638
Don't say "nothing."

141
00:08:54,597 --> 00:08:55,556
Or "anything."

142
00:08:56,682 --> 00:08:58,309
If I buy whatever I please,

143
00:08:58,392 --> 00:09:00,603
you might end up with something bizarre.

144
00:09:00,686 --> 00:09:02,688
I want to receive a bizarre gift.

145
00:09:02,772 --> 00:09:04,565
Oh, no, no, no.

146
00:09:06,359 --> 00:09:08,444
Stop being all lovey-dovey
and hurry up already!

147
00:09:08,527 --> 00:09:10,279
-Jeez.
-Hi!

148
00:09:10,905 --> 00:09:12,073
-Hello.
-Hey.

149
00:09:12,156 --> 00:09:13,658
I'm freezing.

150
00:09:13,741 --> 00:09:14,742
What are we having?

151
00:09:14,825 --> 00:09:18,329
Let's have something fancy
with green stuff sprinkled on top.

152
00:09:18,412 --> 00:09:19,580
I don't like food like that.

153
00:09:19,664 --> 00:09:21,207
They say women like that kind of food.

154
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:22,541
How much are you spending?

155
00:09:23,376 --> 00:09:24,418
How much should I spend?

156
00:09:25,503 --> 00:09:26,671
-I know a place. Let's go.
-What?

157
00:09:26,754 --> 00:09:28,172
Don't worry. It's not expensive.

158
00:09:28,923 --> 00:09:32,343
By the way, are you heading
to the police station or something?

159
00:09:32,426 --> 00:09:34,970
I probably will soon.

160
00:09:35,054 --> 00:09:36,263
I'm trying out the outfit in advance.

161
00:09:36,347 --> 00:09:37,181
Police-station vibe.

162
00:09:37,807 --> 00:09:38,641
Police-station look.

163
00:09:38,724 --> 00:09:40,768
We could've gone somewhere more expensive!

164
00:09:40,851 --> 00:09:43,270
-It's expensive here!
-Hello.

165
00:09:43,354 --> 00:09:44,730
-Hey, nachos!
-Thank you.

166
00:09:44,814 --> 00:09:45,940
Enjoy.

167
00:09:53,572 --> 00:09:54,990
Hi, Mom.

168
00:09:55,074 --> 00:09:55,908
Yeah.

169
00:09:57,076 --> 00:09:58,703
Grandma gets discharged next week.

170
00:10:00,746 --> 00:10:02,039
She's okay.

171
00:10:02,123 --> 00:10:03,457
She can walk a bit now.

172
00:10:04,417 --> 00:10:07,378
Mom, I'm out right now,
so I'll call you when I get home.

173
00:10:07,962 --> 00:10:08,796
Bye.

174
00:10:10,464 --> 00:10:13,217
I thought you said
you were on bad terms with your mom.

175
00:10:13,843 --> 00:10:15,094
She's my stepmom.

176
00:10:16,846 --> 00:10:18,222
You have a stepmom too?

177
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,016
Then what about your grandmother?

178
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,184
She's my stepmom's mom.

179
00:10:23,394 --> 00:10:24,437
Then what about your dad?

180
00:10:25,438 --> 00:10:26,439
He passed away.

181
00:10:28,107 --> 00:10:29,275
When did he pass away?

182
00:10:30,109 --> 00:10:31,193
When I was in the 8th grade.

183
00:10:33,487 --> 00:10:36,157
Have the three of you
lived together ever since?

184
00:10:36,741 --> 00:10:37,575
Yes.

185
00:10:38,492 --> 00:10:40,870
My stepmom is mostly in Japan for work.

186
00:10:43,456 --> 00:10:45,082
They sound like good people.

187
00:10:45,166 --> 00:10:46,167
And you're a good person too.

188
00:10:47,042 --> 00:10:50,379
You see, a relationship doesn't last
if only one side is good.

189
00:10:50,463 --> 00:10:51,505
I get it.

190
00:10:52,131 --> 00:10:54,800
Even in a newly formed family,
you don't become strangers overnight

191
00:10:54,884 --> 00:10:56,010
just because a connection is lost.

192
00:10:56,093 --> 00:10:57,803
You shared a life, after all.

193
00:10:58,804 --> 00:11:01,390
Oh Jeong-hui and I
lost our connection a long time ago.

194
00:11:02,349 --> 00:11:03,267
And my dad…

195
00:11:04,852 --> 00:11:06,604
has a lot of problems.

196
00:11:09,356 --> 00:11:12,902
This mother-daughter relationship
might end at any moment now.

197
00:11:16,405 --> 00:11:17,239
There's a chance

198
00:11:18,157 --> 00:11:19,033
my name…

199
00:11:20,534 --> 00:11:22,244
will be all over the internet.

200
00:11:23,704 --> 00:11:25,080
I just hope I don't get too scared.

201
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:29,210
All right.

202
00:11:29,877 --> 00:11:32,463
I'll take on
all the misfortune in the world,

203
00:11:32,546 --> 00:11:33,964
so make it big, okay?

204
00:11:34,048 --> 00:11:35,257
All of you make it big, okay?

205
00:11:35,341 --> 00:11:36,634
Hwang Dong-man.

206
00:11:36,717 --> 00:11:37,551
Byeon Eun-a.

207
00:11:37,635 --> 00:11:38,677
Lee Jun-hwan.

208
00:11:39,386 --> 00:11:41,180
Everyone, make it big!

209
00:11:41,263 --> 00:11:43,933
-Make it big!
-Make it big!

210
00:11:44,016 --> 00:11:45,809
-Oh, come on!
-Don't lie!

211
00:11:46,727 --> 00:11:49,063
Come on, you're exaggerating!

212
00:11:49,730 --> 00:11:51,774
Jeez, they're laughing so damn loud.

213
00:11:51,857 --> 00:11:52,816
Be quiet.

214
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:54,568
We can't be outdone!

215
00:11:54,652 --> 00:11:55,945
-One, two, three!
-Two, three!

216
00:12:06,455 --> 00:12:09,041
The name of a target appeared, but…

217
00:12:09,124 --> 00:12:09,959
NATIONAL STRESS MANAGEMENT DEPARTMENT

218
00:12:16,465 --> 00:12:18,634
<i>It's the country's</i>
<i>most notorious nutcase politician</i>

219
00:12:19,969 --> 00:12:22,888
<i>who's raising everyone's blood pressure</i>
<i>and must be taken out quickly.</i>

220
00:12:24,223 --> 00:12:25,057
<i>But…</i>

221
00:12:26,308 --> 00:12:27,393
<i>it's his wife.</i>

222
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:37,820
<i>She might be a nutcase,</i>
<i>but she's still his wife.</i>

223
00:12:37,903 --> 00:12:39,530
<i>He can't just let her die, can he?</i>

224
00:12:45,953 --> 00:12:46,996
<i>But then</i>

225
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:51,375
<i>she says the one line</i>
<i>that really pisses off the protagonist</i>

226
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:55,546
<i>and makes him say, "Screw it. Just die."</i>

227
00:12:55,629 --> 00:12:56,755
<i>What could it be?</i>

228
00:13:00,551 --> 00:13:02,136
<i>What could it be?</i>

229
00:13:04,597 --> 00:13:05,556
What did you say?

230
00:13:07,224 --> 00:13:08,309
When will the script be ready?

231
00:13:08,392 --> 00:13:09,727
When will the script be ready?

232
00:13:11,895 --> 00:13:14,898
We were supposed to give them
episodes three and four ages ago.

233
00:13:25,159 --> 00:13:27,161
Stop struggling with them.

234
00:13:27,244 --> 00:13:29,121
Just hand them over and get it over with.

235
00:13:30,873 --> 00:13:32,583
I could think of so many moments

236
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:34,501
that would piss off the protagonist
if he were a writer.

237
00:13:34,585 --> 00:13:37,129
Why did I make him
a Grade 9 civil servant?

238
00:13:37,212 --> 00:13:38,047
Say what?

239
00:13:40,257 --> 00:13:42,051
His friend gets flagged as a target.

240
00:13:44,094 --> 00:13:46,722
All of the memories
and history they shared

241
00:13:46,805 --> 00:13:48,932
flash before his eyes.

242
00:13:50,267 --> 00:13:52,353
He gets choked up. He can't stand it.

243
00:13:52,436 --> 00:13:53,812
He's trying to save them,

244
00:13:53,896 --> 00:13:55,356
but then they ask,

245
00:13:56,106 --> 00:13:58,108
"When will the script be ready?"

246
00:13:58,734 --> 00:14:00,569
"What the… What did you just say?"

247
00:14:00,653 --> 00:14:01,820
"'When will the script be ready?'"

248
00:14:02,571 --> 00:14:06,200
He told them not to say that one thing,
but they said it anyway.

249
00:14:06,283 --> 00:14:08,202
He tells them,
"I'm talking to you right now,

250
00:14:08,285 --> 00:14:10,537
but 99% of my brain
is focused on the script."

251
00:14:10,621 --> 00:14:13,457
"I'm running on the last 1% of my brain,

252
00:14:14,625 --> 00:14:18,295
doing everything I can to keep you alive,

253
00:14:18,379 --> 00:14:19,505
but it's no use."

254
00:14:20,589 --> 00:14:22,508
"Just go."

255
00:14:24,385 --> 00:14:25,552
"Take care."

256
00:14:25,636 --> 00:14:26,470
"I can't see you off."

257
00:14:35,479 --> 00:14:38,107
There are so many moments

258
00:14:38,190 --> 00:14:40,901
when writers get so pissed off
that they just give up.

259
00:14:41,402 --> 00:14:44,405
I just thought of a rage trigger
for the protagonist!

260
00:14:48,117 --> 00:14:49,618
"You only make two million won a month?"

261
00:14:53,831 --> 00:14:54,665
That's it.

262
00:14:56,917 --> 00:14:58,711
"You only make two million won a month?"

263
00:14:58,794 --> 00:15:01,630
That's it. You're a genius, Writer Park.

264
00:15:01,714 --> 00:15:02,923
You figured it out.

265
00:15:03,007 --> 00:15:03,841
You're a genius.

266
00:15:03,924 --> 00:15:05,300
This is it.

267
00:15:05,384 --> 00:15:08,178
"You only make two million won a month?"

268
00:15:09,138 --> 00:15:11,056
"The protagonist is filled with rage

269
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,891
and finally comes to a decision."

270
00:15:12,975 --> 00:15:15,019
-Bang!
-Bang! And they're dead.

271
00:15:15,102 --> 00:15:17,521
He fires nonstop. All right.

272
00:15:17,604 --> 00:15:18,897
Hold on. Let's think here.

273
00:15:18,981 --> 00:15:21,483
"The protagonist starts shooting
to an excessive degree."

274
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:23,652
"You only make two million won a month?"

275
00:15:23,736 --> 00:15:24,862
"Only two million won a month?"

276
00:15:27,656 --> 00:15:29,908
"There's no point in drawing this out…"

277
00:15:30,576 --> 00:15:32,661
Make it big, Hwang Dong-man!

278
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:34,663
Thank you.

279
00:15:34,747 --> 00:15:38,333
-Make it big!
-Thank you! I'll do my best!

280
00:15:38,417 --> 00:15:39,668
Make it big, Eun-a.

281
00:15:40,419 --> 00:15:42,963
-Make it big.
-Everyone, make it big.

282
00:15:46,050 --> 00:15:47,176
Let's go!

283
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:49,428
Where are we going?

284
00:15:50,054 --> 00:15:51,263
-Where is she going?
-Where?

285
00:15:51,346 --> 00:15:53,223
Where are we going?

286
00:15:56,977 --> 00:15:59,021
Mi-ran!

287
00:15:59,605 --> 00:16:01,315
No! Don't do this, Mi-ran.

288
00:16:01,398 --> 00:16:02,983
-Why not?
-Please don't.

289
00:16:03,067 --> 00:16:04,485
He'll beat me to death.

290
00:16:04,568 --> 00:16:05,903
Okay, okay.

291
00:16:05,986 --> 00:16:06,820
Let's leave.

292
00:16:10,157 --> 00:16:10,991
Don't!

293
00:16:11,075 --> 00:16:12,201
Hwang Dong-man!

294
00:16:27,299 --> 00:16:28,967
She went in!

295
00:16:31,678 --> 00:16:33,222
What do we do?

296
00:16:53,784 --> 00:16:54,827
Just as I expected,

297
00:16:56,328 --> 00:16:57,830
you've been drinking.

298
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:04,336
I had a drink myself.

299
00:17:06,296 --> 00:17:10,717
There was no other way for me to wipe away

300
00:17:12,219 --> 00:17:14,138
the wrong that remains somewhere.

301
00:17:23,105 --> 00:17:24,690
I stopped by because I wanted to see you.

302
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:45,669
She's back.

303
00:17:51,884 --> 00:17:53,886
This is why I told you not to go in.

304
00:17:58,223 --> 00:17:59,516
Just you wait!

305
00:18:00,809 --> 00:18:02,477
You'll be into me before you know it.

306
00:18:10,652 --> 00:18:12,070
Wait for me!

307
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:15,949
<i>The ball goes to the goalkeeper,</i>
<i>Choi Chun-ho.</i>

308
00:18:17,326 --> 00:18:18,202
<i>It got cut off.</i>

309
00:18:18,285 --> 00:18:20,120
<i>Yes, the pass came up short.</i>

310
00:18:21,246 --> 00:18:22,247
<i>But the pressure continues.</i>

311
00:18:24,082 --> 00:18:27,252
If you file a lawsuit
and the media gets hold of this,

312
00:18:27,336 --> 00:18:29,129
it's a given that both sides
will get screwed.

313
00:18:29,213 --> 00:18:32,216
I don't care if we both get screwed.

314
00:18:33,008 --> 00:18:34,051
It's not just you two.

315
00:18:34,718 --> 00:18:37,304
-What about Jung Hyeon-u?
-He has nothing to do with this!

316
00:18:37,387 --> 00:18:38,889
It was a fight between Jang Mi-ran and me.

317
00:18:38,972 --> 00:18:41,433
You think she'll stay quiet
about why you guys fought?

318
00:18:41,516 --> 00:18:43,101
She'll disclose every last detail.

319
00:18:45,437 --> 00:18:47,564
Jang Mi-ran was 100% at fault
for what she did.

320
00:18:47,648 --> 00:18:49,608
We'll make her apologize,

321
00:18:50,609 --> 00:18:52,236
so let's settle this for 100 million won.

322
00:18:52,319 --> 00:18:53,362
SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT

323
00:18:55,948 --> 00:18:57,407
You think I'm doing this for money?

324
00:18:57,491 --> 00:18:58,533
You know what?

325
00:18:59,451 --> 00:19:02,496
Even if I killed her,
it still wouldn't be enough!

326
00:19:02,579 --> 00:19:04,706
Even if it means humiliating myself

327
00:19:04,790 --> 00:19:07,042
by admitting
I got beaten up like an idiot,

328
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:09,086
I'm going to take Jang Mi-ran down
for good.

329
00:19:09,711 --> 00:19:11,880
I'll never accept a payoff

330
00:19:13,298 --> 00:19:14,466
and pretend it never happened.

331
00:19:17,177 --> 00:19:19,012
Why aren't you saying anything?

332
00:19:19,846 --> 00:19:22,683
Of course, we'll file a lawsuit, but…

333
00:19:24,810 --> 00:19:27,187
Let's do it a bit later.

334
00:19:27,271 --> 00:19:29,106
My drama is out right now,

335
00:19:29,189 --> 00:19:31,024
and I'm going to Taiwan next week
to promote it.

336
00:19:37,406 --> 00:19:39,449
Jung Hyeon-u is a fool.

337
00:19:40,117 --> 00:19:43,161
He should've insisted on
going after Jang Mi-ran.

338
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:46,540
This makes things difficult.

339
00:19:50,168 --> 00:19:53,130
What makes a woman
grab another woman by their hair?

340
00:19:54,131 --> 00:19:56,758
I've seen it in dramas
but never in real life.

341
00:19:57,467 --> 00:19:58,593
I regret it too.

342
00:19:59,219 --> 00:20:00,595
Grabbing her hair was lame.

343
00:20:01,430 --> 00:20:03,932
Next time,
I'll hit her with a roundhouse kick.

344
00:20:04,016 --> 00:20:05,726
Don't be so stubborn.

345
00:20:06,768 --> 00:20:08,770
You may never get to act again.

346
00:20:09,479 --> 00:20:10,647
You know,

347
00:20:11,273 --> 00:20:12,899
I just want it all out in the open.

348
00:20:12,983 --> 00:20:16,236
I want everything revealed
about how this whole mess started

349
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:18,739
and put it out there for the world to see.

350
00:20:19,573 --> 00:20:20,615
"Jung Hyeon-u…

351
00:20:22,242 --> 00:20:23,368
liked…

352
00:20:24,786 --> 00:20:25,787
Jang Mi-ran."

353
00:20:27,831 --> 00:20:28,749
"Jang Mi-ran…

354
00:20:30,167 --> 00:20:31,209
isn't…

355
00:20:32,502 --> 00:20:33,378
a crazy bitch."

356
00:20:41,094 --> 00:20:43,555
-Tell them I want to see them.
-I will.

357
00:20:44,139 --> 00:20:46,391
What about the <i>Knock knock knock</i> contract?

358
00:20:46,475 --> 00:20:47,601
It'll come through soon.

359
00:21:00,405 --> 00:21:01,656
Welcome.

360
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:02,657
Come in.

361
00:21:06,411 --> 00:21:07,371
Take a seat.

362
00:21:10,582 --> 00:21:11,917
Here, try this.

363
00:21:17,422 --> 00:21:20,425
I wondered why you never backed down
when I was on your case

364
00:21:21,218 --> 00:21:23,428
and what made you act so defiant.

365
00:21:24,304 --> 00:21:25,597
You had an ace up your sleeve.

366
00:21:28,016 --> 00:21:29,434
When did you start writing?

367
00:21:30,352 --> 00:21:31,645
Have you written a lot?

368
00:21:34,189 --> 00:21:35,190
No.

369
00:21:35,899 --> 00:21:36,817
How many have you written?

370
00:21:38,026 --> 00:21:39,069
Not many.

371
00:21:40,278 --> 00:21:41,196
I knew it.

372
00:21:42,489 --> 00:21:44,157
I have a good eye for things.

373
00:21:44,866 --> 00:21:46,660
I called you "Ax," didn't I?

374
00:21:46,743 --> 00:21:48,120
Golden Ax.

375
00:21:48,829 --> 00:21:50,122
There was something different

376
00:21:50,205 --> 00:21:52,165
about the things you said
compared to other producers.

377
00:21:52,249 --> 00:21:55,419
There are things only someone
who's actually written can say.

378
00:21:55,502 --> 00:21:56,878
If you haven't written, you wouldn't know.

379
00:22:01,007 --> 00:22:02,300
Let's keep the fact that you're Yeong-sil

380
00:22:04,094 --> 00:22:05,053
just between you and me.

381
00:22:06,596 --> 00:22:09,933
You know that Ma Jae-yeong
desperately tried to hide you, right?

382
00:22:10,016 --> 00:22:13,311
And it's not like I don't know why
he tried to do so.

383
00:22:13,979 --> 00:22:15,856
He's already on edge as it is.

384
00:22:15,939 --> 00:22:18,358
Nothing good will come
from provoking the director.

385
00:22:19,734 --> 00:22:23,113
<i>Knock knock knock</i> will go under his name,
and he'll pay you.

386
00:22:23,780 --> 00:22:24,698
And let's sign

387
00:22:25,907 --> 00:22:27,409
a separate writer's contract.

388
00:22:29,703 --> 00:22:30,871
I'll pay you top rate.

389
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:34,583
You know me.

390
00:22:35,917 --> 00:22:37,294
I never miss out on a sure bet.

391
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,965
I'll only write
when I have something to write.

392
00:22:43,341 --> 00:22:44,593
I won't write for money.

393
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:47,888
You're so cool.

394
00:22:50,432 --> 00:22:51,766
But you know,

395
00:22:52,726 --> 00:22:54,603
writing comes from
the sense of repaying a debt.

396
00:22:55,353 --> 00:22:58,064
You know Writer Park who wrote <i>The Fools</i>?

397
00:22:58,148 --> 00:23:00,650
After gambling away their signing fee,

398
00:23:00,734 --> 00:23:04,321
they couldn't pay up,
so they wrote nonstop and came up with it.

399
00:23:04,404 --> 00:23:06,031
It ended up being a big hit.

400
00:23:06,615 --> 00:23:07,991
Money makes writing happen.

401
00:23:09,367 --> 00:23:11,077
Without money, it doesn't happen.

402
00:23:12,996 --> 00:23:13,997
How about 100 million won per screenplay?

403
00:23:18,084 --> 00:23:19,669
Let's sign a contract for just two.

404
00:23:23,798 --> 00:23:26,259
You don't have to come to work,

405
00:23:26,343 --> 00:23:28,220
but you can if you want.

406
00:23:28,303 --> 00:23:29,346
Do whatever suits you.

407
00:23:32,599 --> 00:23:35,685
So Writer Park caused a stir overseas too.

408
00:23:35,769 --> 00:23:36,603
Later on,

409
00:23:37,395 --> 00:23:38,605
they wrote it all.

410
00:23:38,688 --> 00:23:41,608
Seasons two, three, and even four.

411
00:23:43,693 --> 00:23:44,527
Hey.

412
00:23:52,369 --> 00:23:53,745
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

413
00:23:57,707 --> 00:23:59,209
Are you on your way back from lunch?

414
00:23:59,793 --> 00:24:01,503
Yes. Looks like you are too.

415
00:24:01,586 --> 00:24:02,420
Yeah.

416
00:24:04,130 --> 00:24:06,716
The key crew is set now, right?

417
00:24:07,342 --> 00:24:09,594
We just need to confirm
the production designer today.

418
00:24:10,345 --> 00:24:11,179
I see.

419
00:24:17,435 --> 00:24:19,604
Why did he act like
he was hiding something?

420
00:24:21,189 --> 00:24:22,482
He looked flustered, right?

421
00:24:24,442 --> 00:24:26,820
I'm not really sure.

422
00:24:29,489 --> 00:24:31,574
What's the deal with them eating together?

423
00:24:32,242 --> 00:24:34,619
-Who?
-Mr. Choi and Byeon Eun-a.

424
00:24:34,703 --> 00:24:36,621
It smelled like they had barbecue.

425
00:24:37,872 --> 00:24:38,915
Really?

426
00:24:54,472 --> 00:24:55,640
ALL THE LUCK TO THE CAST AND CREW
OF VILLAIN HUNT

427
00:24:55,724 --> 00:24:57,058
SUPPORTING NOH KANG-SIK!
FROM HWANG DONG-MAN, KO HYE-JIN

428
00:25:02,147 --> 00:25:04,232
-Please enjoy!
-Thank you.

429
00:25:11,448 --> 00:25:12,615
They built the set well.

430
00:25:13,199 --> 00:25:14,409
Do a better job, you punk!

431
00:25:16,244 --> 00:25:17,412
Give me a break.

432
00:25:18,121 --> 00:25:19,331
"Give me a break"?

433
00:25:20,707 --> 00:25:23,001
You think I don't know what you do?

434
00:25:23,793 --> 00:25:26,421
You intimidate your juniors
to knock them off their game.

435
00:25:26,504 --> 00:25:27,339
-Hello.
-What's wrong?

436
00:25:27,422 --> 00:25:28,840
If your co-star does a good job,

437
00:25:28,923 --> 00:25:30,300
-you do whatever you can
-They got into a fight.

438
00:25:30,383 --> 00:25:32,677
to make sure that scene doesn't get used.

439
00:25:32,761 --> 00:25:34,429
Wow, Jeong-min's good at acting.

440
00:25:36,056 --> 00:25:36,973
He's not acting.

441
00:25:39,768 --> 00:25:40,602
Hey.

442
00:25:41,394 --> 00:25:42,228
Tell me.

443
00:25:43,897 --> 00:25:44,939
You think you're a good actor?

444
00:25:47,609 --> 00:25:48,443
Yes.

445
00:25:50,236 --> 00:25:53,031
Does a good actor
cut off their co-star's flow

446
00:25:53,114 --> 00:25:55,742
and do whatever they want?

447
00:25:55,825 --> 00:26:00,663
You're not confident in your acting!
That's why you're all over the place!

448
00:26:00,747 --> 00:26:03,208
Or maybe it's your old-school acting style

449
00:26:03,291 --> 00:26:07,504
that can't keep up with my range
as an actor.

450
00:26:07,587 --> 00:26:09,631
Are you kidding me?

451
00:26:09,714 --> 00:26:13,134
Let's just focus on acting, okay?

452
00:26:13,218 --> 00:26:14,052
Just acting,

453
00:26:14,552 --> 00:26:16,346
not this hierarchy bullshit.

454
00:26:17,764 --> 00:26:19,432
Hey, show some respect.

455
00:26:19,516 --> 00:26:20,350
Got it?

456
00:26:22,227 --> 00:26:23,228
Got it?

457
00:26:25,939 --> 00:26:27,899
Goddamn it.

458
00:26:27,982 --> 00:26:30,318
Screw this. I'm done here.

459
00:26:30,402 --> 00:26:32,737
Do you really fucking
expect me to shoot this

460
00:26:32,821 --> 00:26:34,864
while getting beaten up at my age?

461
00:26:34,948 --> 00:26:36,866
I'll pay whatever penalty and quit.

462
00:26:37,367 --> 00:26:40,870
It's disgusting how this whole industry
keeps quiet because of guys like him.

463
00:26:40,954 --> 00:26:43,790
I'll call every reporter I know,

464
00:26:43,873 --> 00:26:47,544
tell them all the crap you've pulled,
and leave this industry.

465
00:26:47,627 --> 00:26:50,755
Someone like you should've been
blacklisted a long time ago.

466
00:26:50,839 --> 00:26:52,048
You know that?

467
00:26:52,132 --> 00:26:53,633
Go right ahead.

468
00:26:54,259 --> 00:26:55,093
Do it.

469
00:26:55,176 --> 00:26:56,845
Go ahead and call the reporters, you punk!

470
00:26:56,928 --> 00:26:57,846
Call them now!

471
00:26:57,929 --> 00:26:58,805
Let go of me!

472
00:26:58,888 --> 00:27:00,181
-I said let go of me!
-Hit me.

473
00:27:00,265 --> 00:27:01,391
-Let go of me, you jerks!
-Hit me!

474
00:27:01,474 --> 00:27:02,308
-Go ahead! Hit me!
-Hey!

475
00:27:02,392 --> 00:27:04,269
Hey, stop, stop.

476
00:27:07,522 --> 00:27:08,773
Please calm down.

477
00:27:10,150 --> 00:27:10,984
I mean…

478
00:27:13,736 --> 00:27:14,737
This?

479
00:27:15,447 --> 00:27:17,282
How is this a hit?

480
00:27:17,866 --> 00:27:19,242
Who the hell are you?

481
00:27:19,826 --> 00:27:21,161
I'm sorry.

482
00:27:21,244 --> 00:27:23,246
I get that you're offended.

483
00:27:23,329 --> 00:27:26,458
Then why don't you
just make him feel the same way?

484
00:27:28,376 --> 00:27:31,171
Just do this and make him feel offended.

485
00:27:31,254 --> 00:27:32,922
Come on, it's not that hard to do.

486
00:27:33,006 --> 00:27:34,257
How is this hard?

487
00:27:34,340 --> 00:27:36,843
Have you lost your mind too, you punk?

488
00:27:36,926 --> 00:27:40,263
See? You can see on his face
that he's offended.

489
00:27:40,346 --> 00:27:41,431
-I'm sorry.
-I mean…

490
00:27:41,514 --> 00:27:43,766
-I'm sorry. Let's go.
-Wait, Hye-jin. Hold on.

491
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:47,187
I don't get it. Why are you getting mad
because he offended you?

492
00:27:47,270 --> 00:27:49,814
You just need to offend him right back!

493
00:27:50,315 --> 00:27:53,401
Why would you threaten to quit
and talk to reporters

494
00:27:53,485 --> 00:27:54,652
over something like this?

495
00:27:54,736 --> 00:27:56,988
Again, who the hell are you?

496
00:27:57,071 --> 00:27:58,114
I'm sorry.

497
00:27:58,198 --> 00:27:59,199
Let's go!

498
00:27:59,282 --> 00:28:01,326
-I said let's go!
-I heard you!

499
00:28:01,409 --> 00:28:04,579
Call the reporters,
but at least wait until after my film!

500
00:28:04,662 --> 00:28:06,664
Wait until I'm done with my film!

501
00:28:07,332 --> 00:28:08,917
Come on, don't you agree?

502
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:11,794
Do you know how hard I worked
to get to this point?

503
00:28:12,378 --> 00:28:13,463
That's enough, you bastard!

504
00:28:13,546 --> 00:28:14,756
I ought to just…

505
00:28:17,509 --> 00:28:18,343
You know what?

506
00:28:18,885 --> 00:28:20,678
-I'm not offended.
-For goodness' sake.

507
00:28:20,762 --> 00:28:22,388
What's there to get offended about?

508
00:28:41,491 --> 00:28:42,867
When I tell people

509
00:28:44,285 --> 00:28:46,162
that Hwang Dong-man is the director

510
00:28:46,246 --> 00:28:48,081
and the lead actor is Noh Kang-sik,

511
00:28:48,665 --> 00:28:49,958
everyone says the same thing.

512
00:28:50,500 --> 00:28:52,001
"Oh no, Ms. Ko."

513
00:28:52,752 --> 00:28:54,671
"That'll take years off your life."

514
00:28:56,589 --> 00:28:59,050
I refuse to work myself into anything
that leads to cancer.

515
00:29:01,219 --> 00:29:02,303
Remember what I said?

516
00:29:03,638 --> 00:29:05,139
I plan to live to 100.

517
00:29:06,683 --> 00:29:09,227
If I think it might give me cancer,
I'll scrap it immediately.

518
00:29:11,062 --> 00:29:13,773
So just shut up and stay still!

519
00:29:13,857 --> 00:29:15,942
Don't do anything or say anything!

520
00:29:16,025 --> 00:29:17,569
And don't step in.

521
00:29:17,652 --> 00:29:19,612
Nothing improves when you step in!

522
00:29:20,446 --> 00:29:22,699
Just say, "Ready, action, cut." Okay?

523
00:29:24,325 --> 00:29:25,159
Okay.

524
00:29:36,045 --> 00:29:40,383
Why did you and Mr. Choi
have lunch together out of nowhere?

525
00:29:41,259 --> 00:29:42,677
Did you tell him you're quitting?

526
00:29:43,636 --> 00:29:46,723
He goes hard on people, but the second
someone says they're quitting,

527
00:29:46,806 --> 00:29:48,391
he softens up
and tries to talk them out of it.

528
00:29:50,476 --> 00:29:52,061
What did you two talk about?

529
00:29:53,646 --> 00:29:54,898
Why do you want to know?

530
00:29:56,274 --> 00:29:58,610
Are you anxious
that he's doting on me again?

531
00:29:58,693 --> 00:30:00,445
Watch your mouth, will you?

532
00:30:01,487 --> 00:30:02,488
I'm your senior.

533
00:30:02,572 --> 00:30:03,406
So what?

534
00:30:04,032 --> 00:30:05,158
You can talk to me however you want?

535
00:30:05,241 --> 00:30:07,744
You could've just said
that you somehow ended up eating together.

536
00:30:07,827 --> 00:30:12,165
The way you asked me didn't allow for
such a casual response.

537
00:30:12,916 --> 00:30:13,750
You were being snide.

538
00:30:20,048 --> 00:30:21,799
I won't let her get away with this.

539
00:30:22,300 --> 00:30:25,053
Why does Mr. Choi listen to that brat?

540
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:28,556
She's against changing the protagonist
of <i>Knock knock knock </i>to a woman?

541
00:30:28,640 --> 00:30:30,308
Who does she think she is?

542
00:30:30,391 --> 00:30:34,270
Even the director approved it,
so who the hell is she to object?

543
00:30:35,188 --> 00:30:36,564
Goddamn it.

544
00:30:49,744 --> 00:30:52,205
You've made a lot of progress
in developing it.

545
00:30:53,915 --> 00:30:55,458
Yes, I did.

546
00:30:56,376 --> 00:30:58,127
Let's put a hold on
Jang Mi-ran's contract.

547
00:30:59,170 --> 00:31:00,004
Why all of a sudden?

548
00:31:00,588 --> 00:31:02,715
This is under wraps
because of her current drama,

549
00:31:02,799 --> 00:31:04,759
but something big is about to drop.

550
00:31:04,842 --> 00:31:05,885
What is it?

551
00:31:05,969 --> 00:31:08,179
A criminal lawsuit.

552
00:31:08,262 --> 00:31:09,097
For assault.

553
00:31:09,973 --> 00:31:12,642
I don't think we can cast
Oh Jeong-hui either.

554
00:31:12,725 --> 00:31:13,810
Damn it.

555
00:31:15,395 --> 00:31:16,896
And we don't have Noh Kang-sik.

556
00:31:17,730 --> 00:31:20,108
We can't do <i>Knock knock knock</i>
without Oh Jeong-hui.

557
00:31:21,734 --> 00:31:23,194
Put a hold on her contract for now.

558
00:31:24,445 --> 00:31:25,530
MS. OH JEONG-HUI

559
00:31:25,613 --> 00:31:26,698
This is a mess.

560
00:31:27,573 --> 00:31:28,992
Hello, Ms. Oh!

561
00:31:29,826 --> 00:31:30,702
Right, yes.

562
00:31:31,911 --> 00:31:33,913
Goodness, we're not stalling.

563
00:31:33,997 --> 00:31:35,999
Of course, we want you.

564
00:31:36,082 --> 00:31:36,916
Absolutely.

565
00:31:37,792 --> 00:31:39,210
It's nothing major,

566
00:31:40,545 --> 00:31:43,506
but there's been some talk
about changing the protagonist to a woman

567
00:31:43,589 --> 00:31:45,341
since it'll shift the mood entirely.

568
00:31:46,843 --> 00:31:47,802
The writer did.

569
00:31:49,053 --> 00:31:49,971
Yes, Yeong-sil.

570
00:31:50,054 --> 00:31:53,683
We can't completely ignore
what the writer says.

571
00:32:03,026 --> 00:32:05,737
The moment Hyo-jin opens her mouth,

572
00:32:05,820 --> 00:32:07,822
I'm bored to death.

573
00:32:10,158 --> 00:32:12,118
Every single word is boring.

574
00:32:13,327 --> 00:32:14,746
She seems like someone

575
00:32:16,039 --> 00:32:17,790
who'll never open up,
no matter how long you know her.

576
00:32:17,874 --> 00:32:20,668
She's not someone
who intentionally hides what's inside…

577
00:32:22,879 --> 00:32:25,381
but someone who doesn't know
how to communicate what's inside.

578
00:32:27,425 --> 00:32:29,761
How can a person like that
be in filmmaking?

579
00:32:31,471 --> 00:32:34,390
I'm in The Eight Club with her,

580
00:32:35,099 --> 00:32:38,603
but I've only talked to her
for maybe ten minutes at most.

581
00:32:39,812 --> 00:32:42,148
-It's awkward when I'm alone with her.
-Right?

582
00:32:42,231 --> 00:32:43,066
Yes.

583
00:32:43,149 --> 00:32:45,318
When she starts talking,

584
00:32:46,569 --> 00:32:49,697
I hate the thought of the sound
of her voice touching me in any way,

585
00:32:49,781 --> 00:32:52,408
-so my body just stiffens up.
-Right.

586
00:32:52,492 --> 00:32:53,910
-And I can't hear anything.
-Right.

587
00:32:53,993 --> 00:32:56,245
-It's like my ears automatically shut off.
-I hate it.

588
00:32:56,829 --> 00:32:58,539
But when I talk to you,

589
00:32:59,624 --> 00:33:01,334
it feels like we have a real conversation.

590
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:05,254
I'm so moved.

591
00:33:06,380 --> 00:33:09,133
People always say I talk nonstop
and that I can't hold a conversation.

592
00:33:09,717 --> 00:33:10,927
You do talk nonstop.

593
00:33:12,178 --> 00:33:13,513
Right.

594
00:33:13,596 --> 00:33:16,432
When we meet,
you do 80% of the talking on your own.

595
00:33:16,516 --> 00:33:18,059
Right, on my own.

596
00:33:18,893 --> 00:33:20,478
But it's never boring.

597
00:33:21,395 --> 00:33:22,855
Everything you say really hits me.

598
00:33:23,439 --> 00:33:25,066
And my ears open up.

599
00:33:25,149 --> 00:33:27,777
Sometimes, it's to the point
where I want to take notes.

600
00:33:30,822 --> 00:33:33,324
I had planned
to keep my mouth shut for a while

601
00:33:34,242 --> 00:33:35,451
because I got really chewed out today.

602
00:33:35,535 --> 00:33:37,745
No, don't keep your mouth shut.

603
00:33:37,829 --> 00:33:39,997
Yes, ma'am! I won't keep my mouth shut!

604
00:33:40,081 --> 00:33:41,624
At least, not in front of you.

605
00:33:47,672 --> 00:33:49,924
I feel like I can finally breathe
when I talk to you.

606
00:33:50,925 --> 00:33:53,928
It feels like everything you say
is what I would say,

607
00:33:54,554 --> 00:33:57,807
and you always seem to understand
exactly what I mean.

608
00:34:02,395 --> 00:34:04,272
I'd always get nervous

609
00:34:06,232 --> 00:34:07,817
when talking to people.

610
00:34:11,571 --> 00:34:13,156
I'd wonder,
"How are they taking what I'm saying?"

611
00:34:20,830 --> 00:34:22,665
But when I'm with you,

612
00:34:23,583 --> 00:34:27,336
it feels like my heart bursts open
and everything flows out smoothly

613
00:34:28,421 --> 00:34:30,381
without any hesitation.

614
00:34:32,133 --> 00:34:33,759
I feel the same.

615
00:34:34,886 --> 00:34:36,345
Everything you say
feels like what I would say.

616
00:34:39,140 --> 00:34:41,559
Do you think
we were meant to be one person,

617
00:34:42,185 --> 00:34:44,812
but got split into two
and came into the world?

618
00:34:45,771 --> 00:34:48,649
I would've liked you
even if you were a man,

619
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,277
or even if you were a tree.

620
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:53,905
And if you were the wind,
I would've been nuts about you.

621
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:57,074
Eun-a,

622
00:34:57,867 --> 00:34:59,911
you're too precious to be held

623
00:35:00,536 --> 00:35:03,706
within such a small frame
and a confined space.

624
00:35:04,415 --> 00:35:05,541
I want the whole world

625
00:35:06,083 --> 00:35:07,585
to be Byeon Eun-a.

626
00:35:11,214 --> 00:35:12,131
It's Byeon Eun-a.

627
00:35:13,799 --> 00:35:14,634
It's Byeon Eun-a.

628
00:35:15,593 --> 00:35:16,510
It's Byeon Eun-a.

629
00:35:19,889 --> 00:35:20,723
Eun-a?

630
00:35:21,599 --> 00:35:23,517
Why did you get so small?

631
00:35:23,601 --> 00:35:24,810
Oh dear.

632
00:35:26,103 --> 00:35:27,730
Please take good care of Eun-a.

633
00:35:29,649 --> 00:35:32,193
Oh, Eun-a! Oh no! Eun-a!

634
00:35:34,278 --> 00:35:35,238
Eun-a…

635
00:35:44,538 --> 00:35:46,123
You know,

636
00:35:46,749 --> 00:35:48,501
you give off a teenage boy vibe.

637
00:35:51,629 --> 00:35:52,546
Is that a compliment?

638
00:35:53,130 --> 00:35:54,131
A huge one.

639
00:35:56,008 --> 00:35:57,134
Eun-a.

640
00:35:58,219 --> 00:35:59,637
-Eun-a.
-Eun-a.

641
00:36:03,349 --> 00:36:05,059
Welcome.

642
00:36:12,566 --> 00:36:14,318
Just a second. I'll bring more drinks.

643
00:36:17,697 --> 00:36:18,823
Oh, hello.

644
00:36:18,906 --> 00:36:20,408
-It's been a while.
-Yes, it has.

645
00:36:21,367 --> 00:36:22,952
I hear you're debuting soon?

646
00:36:25,121 --> 00:36:29,125
I've actually been meaning to tell you.

647
00:36:29,208 --> 00:36:30,710
After all, you're the reason I'm here,

648
00:36:31,294 --> 00:36:34,088
and you taught me how to write.

649
00:36:34,755 --> 00:36:38,217
So I really wanted to tell you
that I was debuting.

650
00:36:38,301 --> 00:36:39,468
Thank you!

651
00:36:41,887 --> 00:36:45,683
I worked with Ms. Oh for a bit
a long time ago.

652
00:36:45,766 --> 00:36:47,018
It was

653
00:36:47,101 --> 00:36:50,104
a very embarrassing memory,
so I don't usually talk about it.

654
00:36:50,187 --> 00:36:52,189
I worked on the directing team
for <i>Dogs and Cats</i>.

655
00:36:52,773 --> 00:36:55,693
Oh, this is Producer Byeon Eun-a
from Choi Film.

656
00:36:55,776 --> 00:36:56,610
Let me introduce…

657
00:36:56,694 --> 00:36:57,695
Sit down.

658
00:36:58,612 --> 00:37:00,114
Right, let's sit down.

659
00:37:01,490 --> 00:37:03,200
-Would you like a drink--
-No, thank you.

660
00:37:06,537 --> 00:37:09,874
I heard the writer of <i>Knock knock knock</i>
is against casting me in the role.

661
00:37:10,750 --> 00:37:12,877
I'd like to know why you're against it,

662
00:37:13,627 --> 00:37:14,712
Ms. Yeong-sil.

663
00:37:19,008 --> 00:37:21,552
Are you against
changing the protagonist to a woman,

664
00:37:22,219 --> 00:37:24,597
or are you against me playing the role?

665
00:37:26,474 --> 00:37:29,101
Just give it to me straight.
That's why I'm here.

666
00:37:35,358 --> 00:37:36,275
She wouldn't be

667
00:37:36,942 --> 00:37:38,027
against it.

668
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:40,237
Right?

669
00:37:44,950 --> 00:37:47,328
Which is scarier?
A crazy woman or a crazy man?

670
00:37:48,371 --> 00:37:52,375
Between a crazy woman and a crazy man
roaming the streets,

671
00:37:53,125 --> 00:37:54,377
which is scarier?

672
00:37:55,586 --> 00:37:58,255
Wouldn't a strong man who could harm me…

673
00:38:00,549 --> 00:38:01,967
be scarier?

674
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:06,055
Which is scarier?
A female ghost or a male ghost?

675
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:07,681
Fear…

676
00:38:09,433 --> 00:38:11,143
is an emotional state,

677
00:38:11,227 --> 00:38:12,269
not a physical one.

678
00:38:13,229 --> 00:38:14,980
If strong men are scary,

679
00:38:15,064 --> 00:38:18,150
are all horror film protagonists
supposed to be men?

680
00:38:18,901 --> 00:38:21,654
I thought you were savvy,
but you're surprisingly narrow-minded.

681
00:38:22,988 --> 00:38:26,075
Your objection to changing
to a female protagonist isn't valid.

682
00:38:28,369 --> 00:38:30,454
Is there a personal reason
you object to casting me?

683
00:38:37,753 --> 00:38:38,838
Because it's sickening.

684
00:38:43,634 --> 00:38:45,553
That disgusting ambition of yours

685
00:38:46,929 --> 00:38:48,222
that knows no limits

686
00:38:49,557 --> 00:38:50,808
and keeps pushing its way in.

687
00:38:53,436 --> 00:38:55,771
I want you to know
you can't have everything.

688
00:38:56,939 --> 00:38:58,315
No matter how good they act,

689
00:38:58,816 --> 00:39:01,944
the actor's own emotions
still come through.

690
00:39:03,821 --> 00:39:04,989
It's always a battle.

691
00:39:06,907 --> 00:39:07,908
You have to outshine others.

692
00:39:07,992 --> 00:39:09,785
It's always more, more, more.

693
00:39:12,413 --> 00:39:15,374
Have you ever acted in a supporting role?

694
00:39:16,667 --> 00:39:18,419
Have you ever once enjoyed working?

695
00:39:19,336 --> 00:39:21,755
Enjoy working? Do I look like an amateur?

696
00:39:25,676 --> 00:39:28,137
I believe Daniel Day-Lewis
worked as a shoemaker.

697
00:39:29,305 --> 00:39:31,599
You have to reach the end
to know there's nothing special

698
00:39:31,682 --> 00:39:32,766
before you take a different path.

699
00:39:33,350 --> 00:39:34,602
Don't tell me to become a shoemaker

700
00:39:34,685 --> 00:39:36,687
when I haven't even reached
the end of my path yet.

701
00:39:37,271 --> 00:39:41,525
If someone says money isn't a big deal,
do you agree and give in?

702
00:39:42,109 --> 00:39:45,446
It's not too late to make money
and come to that decision on your own.

703
00:39:46,238 --> 00:39:47,364
It's the same thing.

704
00:39:47,448 --> 00:39:49,200
You have to reach the end of hell to know.

705
00:40:05,799 --> 00:40:07,176
Do you even know what hell is?

706
00:40:16,977 --> 00:40:19,396
You can go through hell
at just nine years old.

707
00:40:21,982 --> 00:40:24,276
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>It's taboo to talk about her.</i>

708
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:26,028
Oh, I know her name.

709
00:40:26,111 --> 00:40:27,321
It's Byeon Si-on.

710
00:40:27,404 --> 00:40:29,365
Which sounds better,
Byeon Si-on or Byeon Eun-a?

711
00:40:39,291 --> 00:40:41,377
It's not true. Right, Eun-a?

712
00:40:43,921 --> 00:40:47,758
Take a look at every line you've written
and your desire to kill in each one.

713
00:40:48,384 --> 00:40:51,345
Your motivation is fueled
by your hatred for me.

714
00:40:52,930 --> 00:40:56,267
They say you can't blame parents
once you turn 40.

715
00:40:56,350 --> 00:40:58,352
What will you use as motivation then?

716
00:41:00,813 --> 00:41:02,523
How's your grandmother doing?

717
00:41:06,527 --> 00:41:11,115
Anyone who absolutely detests something
also has something they absolutely love.

718
00:41:11,198 --> 00:41:12,199
It's how they live on.

719
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:27,423
As soon as I was born,
I was abandoned every day.

720
00:41:28,507 --> 00:41:29,967
Your deep sigh,

721
00:41:30,050 --> 00:41:31,594
your look…

722
00:41:34,054 --> 00:41:35,431
Even if it kills me…

723
00:41:37,933 --> 00:41:40,853
I want to show you how wrong you were.

724
00:41:40,936 --> 00:41:43,188
Just write it all down and give it to me.

725
00:41:43,272 --> 00:41:46,483
Write down everything you remember
about how much of a bitch I was.

726
00:41:47,067 --> 00:41:49,903
You can write a hundred pages
or a thousand, and I'll read it.

727
00:41:49,987 --> 00:41:53,907
I'll read it every day
like it's a daily Bible verse.

728
00:41:53,991 --> 00:41:56,285
I'll repent while reading it.

729
00:41:57,119 --> 00:41:59,913
I'll spend the rest of my life

730
00:41:59,997 --> 00:42:02,583
dwelling on that precious wound
you can't seem to let go!

731
00:42:02,666 --> 00:42:03,500
So you just write it down

732
00:42:04,126 --> 00:42:05,419
and be done with it!

733
00:42:08,505 --> 00:42:11,050
Some writers keep reliving their own pain.

734
00:42:11,967 --> 00:42:14,428
You used all of your hatred for me
in writing <i>Knock knock knock</i>.

735
00:42:14,511 --> 00:42:16,305
There's nothing left to write about it,

736
00:42:16,388 --> 00:42:18,057
so just let it go and move on!

737
00:42:19,391 --> 00:42:22,811
Stop rehashing the same emotions
and letting your writing get rusty!

738
00:42:28,233 --> 00:42:29,610
The next round will reveal

739
00:42:30,402 --> 00:42:32,279
what kind of writing Ma Jae-yeong produces

740
00:42:32,363 --> 00:42:34,281
and what kind of writing
Yeong-sil produces.

741
00:42:35,574 --> 00:42:39,244
It'll determine who <i>Knock knock knock</i>
originally belonged to.

742
00:43:22,454 --> 00:43:25,082
You used all of your hatred for me
in writing <i>Knock knock knock</i>.

743
00:43:25,165 --> 00:43:26,792
There's nothing left to write about it,

744
00:43:26,875 --> 00:43:28,711
so just let it go and move on!

745
00:43:29,586 --> 00:43:33,590
<i>If you could erase your childhood memories</i>
<i>to escape from this pain,</i>

746
00:43:34,258 --> 00:43:35,134
<i>would you do it?</i>

747
00:43:37,511 --> 00:43:38,512
No.

748
00:43:41,932 --> 00:43:44,059
Without this pain, that woman…

749
00:43:45,644 --> 00:43:47,646
<i>would be completely innocent.</i>

750
00:43:59,950 --> 00:44:03,537
<i>She was neglected</i>
<i>and grew up without her parents.</i>

751
00:44:04,079 --> 00:44:05,748
<i>I didn't think much of it at the time,</i>

752
00:44:05,831 --> 00:44:08,792
<i>but looking back now,</i>
<i>my heart simply goes out to her.</i>

753
00:44:09,793 --> 00:44:11,211
<i>I wonder what she's doing now</i>

754
00:44:11,962 --> 00:44:13,380
<i>and how her life is going.</i>

755
00:44:14,798 --> 00:44:17,593
<i>That sloppy </i>gimbap

756
00:44:17,676 --> 00:44:19,511
<i>she clearly made herself.</i>

757
00:44:20,429 --> 00:44:22,222
<i>I still think about that sad </i>gimbap

758
00:44:23,015 --> 00:44:25,392
<i>and how she forced it down.</i>

759
00:44:30,814 --> 00:44:31,648
NO WAY, LOOK AT THIS

760
00:44:31,732 --> 00:44:32,775
POOR THING… THE KID DIDN'T DESERVE THIS

761
00:44:36,236 --> 00:44:37,446
<i>Has it ever occurred to you</i>

762
00:44:37,529 --> 00:44:39,364
<i>that it might be rude</i>
<i>to post something like this?</i>

763
00:44:40,157 --> 00:44:42,785
<i>This child is now an adult.</i>

764
00:44:42,868 --> 00:44:45,078
<i>How would she feel reading this?</i>

765
00:44:48,999 --> 00:44:53,086
<i>What about the pain</i>
<i>of having to relive a childhood</i>

766
00:44:54,338 --> 00:44:56,548
<i>that everyone remembers as pitiful?</i>

767
00:44:57,758 --> 00:44:59,468
<i>You may act sympathetic,</i>

768
00:45:00,093 --> 00:45:01,220
<i>but right now,</i>

769
00:45:01,970 --> 00:45:05,891
<i>you're keeping her trapped</i>
<i>in that painful past and toying with her.</i>

770
00:45:07,142 --> 00:45:08,977
<i>Please don't pretend it's compassion.</i>

771
00:45:09,645 --> 00:45:11,772
Don't pretend it's compassion,
you assholes.

772
00:45:27,538 --> 00:45:31,291
NATIONAL STRESS MANAGEMENT DEPARTMENT
EPISODE 4

773
00:45:31,375 --> 00:45:34,545
BY PARK GYEONG-SE, PARK JEONG-MIN

774
00:45:54,481 --> 00:45:56,608
-Hey.
-Did you read the script?

775
00:45:57,484 --> 00:45:58,610
<i>Yeah.</i>

776
00:45:59,236 --> 00:46:00,153
What do you think?

777
00:46:01,363 --> 00:46:02,364
It's fun.

778
00:46:03,156 --> 00:46:04,074
<i>That's it?</i>

779
00:46:04,157 --> 00:46:05,033
What else should I say?

780
00:46:05,617 --> 00:46:06,910
Is it really fun?

781
00:46:07,578 --> 00:46:08,620
Yeah, it is.

782
00:46:08,704 --> 00:46:10,455
Then why are you talking like that?

783
00:46:10,539 --> 00:46:12,082
<i>How should I be talking?</i>

784
00:46:13,625 --> 00:46:15,210
I say it's fun, and you still complain.

785
00:46:16,336 --> 00:46:18,171
<i>Are you attending</i>
<i>Director Lee's premiere later?</i>

786
00:46:19,506 --> 00:46:21,133
No, I want to sleep.

787
00:46:21,216 --> 00:46:22,801
Come to the after-party, then.

788
00:46:22,884 --> 00:46:24,011
<i>Forget it. I'm sleeping.</i>

789
00:46:25,012 --> 00:46:25,846
Bye.

790
00:46:49,911 --> 00:46:51,622
"TRAPPED IN WRONG ANSWERS" AFTER-PARTY

791
00:46:52,789 --> 00:46:53,999
-Hello.
-Hello.

792
00:46:54,082 --> 00:46:57,085
-Why didn't Director Park Gyeong-se come?
-He was up all night, so he's sleeping.

793
00:46:57,169 --> 00:46:59,212
That's a shame. I had a lot to ask him.

794
00:47:00,714 --> 00:47:01,548
Okay, then.

795
00:47:04,885 --> 00:47:07,763
Does your company produce
period pieces as well?

796
00:47:07,846 --> 00:47:08,972
Wait.

797
00:47:14,186 --> 00:47:15,187
Director Park!

798
00:47:15,687 --> 00:47:16,730
Why are you so late?

799
00:47:16,813 --> 00:47:18,815
I was tired so I almost didn't make it.

800
00:47:18,899 --> 00:47:19,816
Oh, really?

801
00:47:20,442 --> 00:47:21,526
Have you eaten?

802
00:47:22,819 --> 00:47:24,154
Please excuse me for a second.

803
00:47:28,283 --> 00:47:30,118
-Feels like quite the party.
-Please dig in.

804
00:47:31,078 --> 00:47:32,037
Oh, hello.

805
00:47:33,038 --> 00:47:35,207
It's very interesting, huh?

806
00:47:35,290 --> 00:47:36,500
Isn't it weird, though?

807
00:47:36,583 --> 00:47:38,043
But I think it'll do well.

808
00:47:38,126 --> 00:47:39,461
Are you sure about that?

809
00:47:52,224 --> 00:47:54,309
Oh, it's Ms. Ko.

810
00:47:55,352 --> 00:47:56,436
Ms. Ko!

811
00:48:11,743 --> 00:48:12,703
When did you get here?

812
00:48:16,498 --> 00:48:17,624
Who are you, sir?

813
00:48:18,208 --> 00:48:20,043
Come on. Are you drunk?

814
00:48:20,627 --> 00:48:21,586
Do you know me?

815
00:48:23,839 --> 00:48:25,340
I don't think we've met before.

816
00:48:26,967 --> 00:48:29,386
What are you doing?
What's with the acting?

817
00:48:29,469 --> 00:48:32,889
Excuse me, but I don't know who you are.

818
00:48:33,515 --> 00:48:36,268
I believe you've got the wrong person.
Can you please leave?

819
00:48:38,437 --> 00:48:40,480
Director Park,
I thought you couldn't come.

820
00:48:43,108 --> 00:48:45,569
Episodes three and four are amazing!

821
00:48:46,194 --> 00:48:47,738
They're more fun than the first two.

822
00:48:47,821 --> 00:48:49,281
That's good to hear.

823
00:48:49,364 --> 00:48:51,700
Everyone in the company is raving about
how <i>National Stress Management Department</i>

824
00:48:51,783 --> 00:48:54,202
has been confirmed
as a long-running series.

825
00:48:55,495 --> 00:48:58,081
You have to sign
a three-season deal with us, okay?

826
00:48:58,165 --> 00:49:00,041
Goodness, three seasons? Come on.

827
00:49:01,001 --> 00:49:02,586
-Just think about it.
-I will.

828
00:49:06,798 --> 00:49:07,841
Excuse me.

829
00:49:08,425 --> 00:49:10,761
Are you Director Park Gyeong-se who wrote
<i>National Stress Management Department</i>?

830
00:49:12,679 --> 00:49:14,765
So you're the one who wrote that.

831
00:49:14,848 --> 00:49:18,059
I'm so sorry for not recognizing you.

832
00:49:18,143 --> 00:49:20,061
Why are you acting like this?

833
00:49:21,605 --> 00:49:23,607
I really enjoyed reading it.

834
00:49:24,191 --> 00:49:25,859
I've read all of your work,

835
00:49:27,277 --> 00:49:30,572
but I think this is your best yet.

836
00:49:31,531 --> 00:49:32,449
I'm sure it'll do well.

837
00:49:40,415 --> 00:49:42,083
Your writing

838
00:49:42,167 --> 00:49:43,585
was full of excitement.

839
00:49:44,252 --> 00:49:45,212
So full of energy!

840
00:49:52,052 --> 00:49:53,637
You must be in love.

841
00:50:05,482 --> 00:50:07,359
Your writing was full of excitement.

842
00:50:11,029 --> 00:50:14,366
For creators,
people are their greatest asset.

843
00:50:15,534 --> 00:50:19,496
Like slash-and-burn farmers
who burn their land to cultivate again,

844
00:50:20,205 --> 00:50:22,082
creators can completely fall for someone

845
00:50:23,250 --> 00:50:24,543
<i>and soak up their words,</i>

846
00:50:25,252 --> 00:50:26,503
<i>their energy,</i>

847
00:50:26,586 --> 00:50:30,590
and everything about them
to get back on their feet.

848
00:50:31,758 --> 00:50:33,093
That's why I think

849
00:50:33,677 --> 00:50:37,806
creators should be allowed to fall in love
a hundred, a thousand times.

850
00:50:42,727 --> 00:50:43,812
I'll support you.

851
00:50:44,813 --> 00:50:47,482
Keep writing with that same excitement
to the very end.

852
00:50:48,149 --> 00:50:48,984
Good luck.

853
00:50:56,908 --> 00:50:57,784
Honey.

854
00:51:00,370 --> 00:51:01,329
Hye-jin.

855
00:51:02,539 --> 00:51:03,915
Damn it.

856
00:51:05,041 --> 00:51:05,917
Ko Hye-jin.

857
00:51:14,593 --> 00:51:16,094
They say the most pitiful person…

858
00:51:18,263 --> 00:51:19,556
is the wife of a director.

859
00:51:21,683 --> 00:51:22,767
But I'm also…

860
00:51:24,728 --> 00:51:26,438
the CEO of a production company.

861
00:51:32,402 --> 00:51:33,695
So be excited.

862
00:51:35,739 --> 00:51:38,158
Keep being excited.

863
00:51:40,410 --> 00:51:41,703
Just write well.

864
00:51:43,246 --> 00:51:45,332
I don't care if you fall into hell

865
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,585
or into a honeypot.

866
00:51:52,422 --> 00:51:54,716
As long as you come back
with some writing,

867
00:51:54,799 --> 00:51:58,011
I'll drag you into hell or shove you
straight into that damn honeypot myself!

868
00:52:03,892 --> 00:52:06,394
So just keep being excited.

869
00:52:14,694 --> 00:52:16,196
Fine, I got excited!

870
00:52:17,405 --> 00:52:20,367
I met a woman who looked at me
the way Ko Hye-jin used to,

871
00:52:20,450 --> 00:52:21,910
so I got excited!

872
00:52:28,458 --> 00:52:30,794
You don't even dote on me anymore!

873
00:52:31,544 --> 00:52:33,046
So how do you expect me to write?

874
00:52:56,027 --> 00:52:57,612
<i>I didn't know what to do,</i>

875
00:52:58,488 --> 00:53:00,115
<i>so I got hammered and went to sleep.</i>

876
00:53:02,033 --> 00:53:03,076
<i>When I got up,</i>

877
00:53:03,952 --> 00:53:05,203
<i>it was dark outside.</i>

878
00:53:07,455 --> 00:53:08,999
<i>Depression presses down on me</i>

879
00:53:10,542 --> 00:53:11,543
<i>like a heavy iron weight.</i>

880
00:53:21,845 --> 00:53:25,098
Who the hell are you
to object to casting Oh Jeong-hui?

881
00:53:25,849 --> 00:53:28,184
You even went behind my back
and told Mr. Choi that you're Yeong-sil.

882
00:53:29,477 --> 00:53:31,271
I'm scrapping this. I won't do it.

883
00:53:31,354 --> 00:53:32,897
I won't!

884
00:53:32,981 --> 00:53:35,108
Speak slowly. I'll hear you out.

885
00:53:35,608 --> 00:53:37,152
The more you run your mouth,

886
00:53:38,361 --> 00:53:39,529
the better it is for me

887
00:53:40,488 --> 00:53:41,573
since I'm recording this.

888
00:53:44,492 --> 00:53:45,994
Overconfident bastard.

889
00:53:47,245 --> 00:53:49,581
You're working on a project
worth hundreds of billions of won

890
00:53:49,664 --> 00:53:51,833
with a bunch of A-list actors,

891
00:53:51,916 --> 00:53:54,210
<i>and you make a call like this</i>
<i>without thinking?</i>

892
00:53:55,211 --> 00:53:57,422
Your voice needs to be
kept on record forever,

893
00:53:58,548 --> 00:54:00,133
so the world never forgets

894
00:54:01,676 --> 00:54:02,844
what kind of person you are.

895
00:54:03,344 --> 00:54:04,512
Someone like you

896
00:54:05,346 --> 00:54:06,890
never should've been born.

897
00:54:26,868 --> 00:54:28,036
Don't come.

898
00:54:29,287 --> 00:54:32,040
The food here is fine. Just get some rest.

899
00:54:33,374 --> 00:54:34,417
I'll go tomorrow.

900
00:54:35,460 --> 00:54:36,294
<i>Lie down.</i>

901
00:54:37,170 --> 00:54:38,338
<i>Go on, lie down.</i>

902
00:54:39,964 --> 00:54:41,174
Watch some TV.

903
00:54:42,050 --> 00:54:42,926
Okay?

904
00:55:12,080 --> 00:55:13,373
I have to give it to you.

905
00:55:13,456 --> 00:55:15,875
You've got a knack for picking up
whatever I throw away.

906
00:55:15,959 --> 00:55:19,129
You picked up Noh Kang-sik, the grant,

907
00:55:19,212 --> 00:55:20,547
and Byeon Eun-a.

908
00:55:21,172 --> 00:55:23,800
Shouldn't you be thanking me
at this point?

909
00:55:27,262 --> 00:55:29,722
You think you sound cool
saying you threw them away?

910
00:55:30,598 --> 00:55:32,016
Just be honest.

911
00:55:33,935 --> 00:55:34,978
You were afraid,

912
00:55:35,645 --> 00:55:36,604
so you deliberately

913
00:55:37,230 --> 00:55:38,398
let go of them.

914
00:55:39,774 --> 00:55:41,568
She shone so brightly,

915
00:55:42,318 --> 00:55:44,112
and you got so scared

916
00:55:45,488 --> 00:55:46,489
that you deliberately

917
00:55:47,157 --> 00:55:49,242
let go of Byeon Eun-a.

918
00:55:51,286 --> 00:55:52,287
Who got scared?

919
00:55:55,165 --> 00:55:56,249
Who shines?

920
00:55:58,376 --> 00:55:59,544
Who?

921
00:56:00,044 --> 00:56:02,922
-Tell me.
-I'm freaking scared too.

922
00:56:04,799 --> 00:56:06,092
But I endure it.

923
00:56:06,176 --> 00:56:08,136
Even if I go blind

924
00:56:08,219 --> 00:56:10,013
from her shiny brightness,

925
00:56:10,638 --> 00:56:12,515
I'm going to keep both eyes open
and endure it.

926
00:56:13,099 --> 00:56:16,102
That's the respect you owe someone
who believes in you, you jackass.

927
00:56:16,186 --> 00:56:17,937
No matter how scared you were,

928
00:56:18,646 --> 00:56:21,816
you shouldn't have turned so evil
when you ran away from her first!

929
00:56:21,900 --> 00:56:23,109
Goddamn it!

930
00:56:25,737 --> 00:56:27,906
Freaking loser. Who do you think you are?

931
00:57:05,610 --> 00:57:07,862
To hell with my movie.

932
00:57:08,446 --> 00:57:10,907
If I don't take you on today,
I'm a freaking moron.

933
00:57:42,146 --> 00:57:43,982
I'll kill you!

934
00:57:53,950 --> 00:57:54,951
Damn it.

935
00:57:57,704 --> 00:57:59,831
<i>You think Byeon Eun-a is someone</i>
<i>you can just throw away?</i>

936
00:58:00,540 --> 00:58:03,626
<i>You can't throw away an ideal</i>
<i>sent by the gods!</i>

937
00:58:03,710 --> 00:58:04,836
<i>You can't!</i>

938
00:58:16,180 --> 00:58:17,890
<i>Just say, "Byeon Eun-a did it!"</i>

939
00:58:17,974 --> 00:58:19,684
<i>"Byeon Eun-a did it!"</i>

940
00:58:19,767 --> 00:58:22,604
<i>Cover the whole world with Byeon Eun-a!</i>

941
00:58:22,687 --> 00:58:25,148
<i>That's the only way</i>
<i>you can escape the hell you're in!</i>

942
00:58:39,537 --> 00:58:40,872
I did it!

943
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:45,293
I did it!

944
00:58:45,376 --> 00:58:47,420
I'm the one who did it!

945
00:58:58,848 --> 00:58:59,807
<i>By the way,</i>

946
00:59:00,808 --> 00:59:02,352
<i>I'm really sorry to say this,</i>

947
00:59:03,686 --> 00:59:05,897
<i>but why does your identity</i>
<i>as Oh Jeong-hui's hidden daughter,</i>

948
00:59:06,773 --> 00:59:09,359
<i>something you find so painful,</i>

949
00:59:10,693 --> 00:59:13,488
<i>feel and look so shiny and bright to me?</i>

950
00:59:19,661 --> 00:59:22,622
<i>I'm just an ordinary person</i>
<i>who can never catch up to you.</i>

951
00:59:24,916 --> 00:59:25,917
<i>Ms. Byeon Eun-a.</i>

952
00:59:26,876 --> 00:59:27,794
<i>It seems</i>

953
00:59:28,628 --> 00:59:31,005
<i>you're determined to rise to the heavens.</i>

954
00:59:45,728 --> 00:59:46,688
God.

955
00:59:53,653 --> 00:59:55,071
Please dote on me.

956
01:01:26,078 --> 01:01:30,166
CLOSED UNTIL THE END OF DECEMBER

957
01:01:56,859 --> 01:01:57,693
What happened?

958
01:01:59,070 --> 01:02:00,279
I was duped.

959
01:02:03,699 --> 01:02:04,617
This leather…

960
01:02:08,704 --> 01:02:11,040
was made in 1998.

961
01:02:15,044 --> 01:02:16,337
The story

962
01:02:16,921 --> 01:02:18,756
about it being worn
by a Russian soldier in World War II…

963
01:02:20,508 --> 01:02:21,676
was a lie.

964
01:02:22,134 --> 01:02:22,969
A lie.

965
01:02:28,850 --> 01:02:33,312
I thought about the Russian soldier
who was shot and killed

966
01:02:33,396 --> 01:02:35,606
and spent my days living
with a tragic sense of purpose.

967
01:02:38,150 --> 01:02:40,403
But I got duped by a handsome guy
at a flea market.

968
01:02:43,698 --> 01:02:45,992
It turns out, even handsome guys lie.

969
01:02:51,914 --> 01:02:52,748
But you know what?

970
01:02:54,625 --> 01:02:55,543
For some reason…

971
01:02:57,211 --> 01:02:58,588
I feel relieved.

972
01:03:01,257 --> 01:03:03,718
I think my life will be
one big comedy to the end,

973
01:03:04,510 --> 01:03:05,469
so I feel relieved.

974
01:03:10,600 --> 01:03:12,435
The protagonist in <i>Joker</i>

975
01:03:12,518 --> 01:03:14,645
thought his life was a tragedy,

976
01:03:14,729 --> 01:03:17,315
but when he found it was a comedy,
he went off the rails.

977
01:03:17,398 --> 01:03:18,274
However…

978
01:03:20,401 --> 01:03:21,360
I like

979
01:03:21,986 --> 01:03:22,820
that it's a comedy.

980
01:03:27,783 --> 01:03:29,619
Life should be a comedy.

981
01:03:31,412 --> 01:03:34,665
Would you mind
if I did a classic comedy bit?

982
01:03:41,839 --> 01:03:43,090
Guess where my tooth is?

983
01:03:46,886 --> 01:03:48,179
It only feels right to do this

984
01:03:48,846 --> 01:03:50,389
since I've lost my tooth.

985
01:04:18,417 --> 01:04:20,211
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

986
01:04:38,354 --> 01:04:40,731
<i>Just so you know,</i>
<i>it's not just women at Eun-a's house.</i>

987
01:04:41,315 --> 01:04:43,859
<i>If you mess with Eun-a,</i>
<i>you'll be in real trouble.</i>

988
01:04:43,943 --> 01:04:45,027
<i>Let's just stop, Dong-man.</i>

989
01:04:45,111 --> 01:04:47,488
<i>I was just saying it for fun.</i>

990
01:04:47,571 --> 01:04:49,198
Let's end this. Damn it.

991
01:04:49,281 --> 01:04:51,784
<i>You can probably do it</i>
<i>without the emotion watch now.</i>

992
01:04:51,867 --> 01:04:52,868
<i>You should give it a try.</i>

993
01:04:52,952 --> 01:04:55,246
<i>Practice accurately identifying emotions.</i>

994
01:04:55,329 --> 01:04:56,414
Why isn't Writer Park here?

995
01:04:56,998 --> 01:04:59,250
<i>Just ignore me and keep writing</i>
<i>with that same excitement.</i>

996
01:05:01,085 --> 01:05:03,295
I'm Director Hwang Dong-man.

997
01:05:03,963 --> 01:05:06,090
<i>Dong-man has gone quiet.</i>

998
01:05:06,173 --> 01:05:07,425
<i>I think he's having a mental breakdown.</i>

999
01:05:08,259 --> 01:05:09,844
<i>Start filming already, you bastard!</i>

1000
01:05:09,927 --> 01:05:10,970
<i>Start filming!</i>

1001
01:05:15,933 --> 01:05:20,938
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim

